erican Soccer League (1968\u20131984) stadiums]]\n[[Category:Olympic football venues]]\n[[Category:Orlando Renegades stadiums]]\n[[Category:Rugby league stadiums in the United States]]\n[[Category:Rugby union stadiums in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Soccer venues in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Sports venues completed in 1961]]\n[[Category:United States Football League venues]]\n[[Category:Venues of the 1996 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Washington Diplomats]]\n[[Category:Washington Nationals stadiums]]\n[[Category:Washington Redskins stadiums]]\n[[Category:Washington Senators (1961\u20131971) stadiums]]\n[[Category:Washington Whips sports facilities|r]]\n[[Category:1994 FIFA World Cup stadiums]]\n[[Category:1961 establishments in Washington, D.C.]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|John F. Kennedy Stadium}}\n{{short description|Multi-purpose stadium in Washington, D.C., United States}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox venue\n| stadium_name        = Robert F. Kennedy Memorial Stadium\n| nickname            = ''RFK''\n| logo_image          = File:RFK Stadium logo.png\n| image               = File:RFK Stadium aerial photo, looking towards Capitol, 1988.jpg\n| caption             = RFK Stadium from the east in [[1988 Washington Redskins season|1988]],<br>looking towards the [[United States Capitol|U.S. Capitol]]\n| location            = [[Washington, D.C.]]\n| coordinates         = {{coord|38.890|N|76.972|W|type:landmark_scale:2000|display=it}}\n| broke_ground        = July 8, 1960<ref name=\"bbt\">{{cite web |title=Robert F. Kennedy Memorial Stadium|url=http://www.ballparktour.com/RFK_Stadium.html|work=Ballpark Tour|access-date=March 11, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130406051839/http://www.ballparktour.com/RFK_Stadium.html|archivedate=April 6, 2013}}</ref>\n| opened              = October 1, 1961<br>({{Years or months ago|1961}})\n| closed              = \n| demolished          =\n| owner               = District of Columbia\n| operato